<item>
            <title>[LU-11661] sanityn: test_47g failed</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11661</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Lai Siyao &amp;lt;lai.siyao@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9599e15e-e68d-11e8-815b-52540065bddc&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9599e15e-e68d-11e8-815b-52540065bddc&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanityn test 47g: pdirops: remote mkdir vs getattr ================================================ 12:51:29 (1542027089)
CMD: onyx-38vm9 lctl set_param fail_loc=0x80000145
fail_loc=0x80000145
stat: cannot stat &apos;/mnt/lustre2/f47g.sanityn&apos;: No such file or directory
 sanityn test_47g: @@@@@@ FAIL: stat must succeed 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:5810:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanityn.sh:2484:test_47g()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6091:run_one()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6130:run_one_logged()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:5977:run_test()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanityn.sh:2490:main()
Dumping lctl log to /autotest/autotest/2018-11-12/lustre-reviews-el7_5-x86_64--review-dne-zfs-part-1--1_9_1__59951___920cef3f-54b2-4cba-9520-05840c0cce19/sanityn.test_47g.*.1542027092.log
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The debug log shows that the sleep before stat is too small, that mkdir is not done yet, increase the sleep time should solve this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
